{"word":"G1080 - γεννάω - gennáō - ghen-nah'-o - Bear","slug":"G1080","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">γεννάω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>gennáō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ghen-nah'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bear"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B3;&#x03B5;&#x03BD;&#x03BD;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - gennao&#x0304;</b> - <i>ghen-nah'-o</i><p/>From a variation of <a href=\"#/G1085\">G1085</a>; to <i>procreate</i> (properly of the father, but by extension of the mother); figuratively to <i>regenerate:</i> - bear, beget, be born, bring forth, conceive, be delivered of, gender, make, spring."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1081\">G1081</a>, <a href=\"#/G1084\">G1084</a>, <a href=\"#/G313\">G313</a>, <a href=\"#/G738\">G738</a>"}]}